<asp:Content ID="Content2" ContentPlaceHolderID="ContentPlaceHolder1" runat="server">
    <div class="dashboard-breadcrumb">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="dashboard-breadcrumb-inner">
                <div class="breadcrumb-left">
                    <h3>Return Policy</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="breadcrumb-right">
                    <a href="index.aspx"><i class="fas fa-home"></i></a>
                    <span> / Return Policy</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container" style="margin-top:40px;">
        <div class="standard-content-box">
            <h1 style="color:#1e293b; font-weight:800; margin:0 0 10px; font-size:2.2rem;">Reverse Logistics</h1>
            <p style="font-size:1.1rem; color:#64748b; margin-bottom:40px;">Transparent frameworks guiding product repatriations and fiscal refunds.</p>
            <hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid #f1f5f9; margin-bottom:40px;" />
            <h2>Validation Window</h2>
            <p>Consumptive parcels retain an absolute 10-day post-delivery evaluation boundary. Return requests initialized past the 240th hour from static delivery timestamp will be automatically negated by algorithmic gatekeepers.</p>
            
            <h2>Integrity Standards</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Original seal mechanics must remain biologically uncompromised.</li>
                <li>Primary packaging grids must avoid deformation or tearing.</li>
                <li>Static SKU identification tags must hold fixed coordinate linkage.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Fiscal Restoration (Refunds)</h2>
            <p>Following inbound verification at center hub, refunds execute instantaneous routing back to the originating fiscal instrument. Normal settlement window rests at 5-7 operational banking cycles depending purely on intermediary routers.</p>

            <h2>Non-Returnable Subsets</h2>
            <p>Undergarments, perishable consumables, custom-imprinted artifacts, and unlocked digital tokens retain static irreversible sale finalization status to safeguard dynamic sanitary thresholds.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</asp:Content>
